		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />You just gave me an idea. You could use this kind of automated process (because it's actually fast - minus the coding it took like 5 minutes) and make a series of picture banks, and swap them every 8-10 frames, and you'd have a detailed movie file, in an NES game. you could have about 20-30 frames - that would be about 3-4 seconds of video. Combine that with a DMC sample and you could have audio and video in sync.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
